  <h1>
   vertex_get_number
  </h1>
  With this function you can find out the number of individual vertices defined in any given vertex buffer.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">vertex_get_number(buffer);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      buffer
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Drawing/Primitives/vertex_create_buffer.htm">
        Vertex Buffer ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The vertex buffer to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">v_num = vertex_get_number(v_buffer);
</code></pre>
  The above code will store the number of vertices stored in the given vertex buffer to a variable.
 </body>
</html>